, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-Semitic *lā. Compare Hebrew לֹא (lo), which, in older texts, is used in the negative imperative and the negative existential indicative."}, "ipa": ["/laː/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n43185", "headword_ar": "لَا", "root": "l", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", the negative, does not necessarily restrict to the signification of future time a marfooa aor. following it: in a case of this kind,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is often substituted for it in the explanation of a phrase; as in the instance of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yaEorifu hir~aA mino bir~K", "text_ar": "لَا يَعْرِفُ هِرَّا مِنْ بِرٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the TA, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "br", "text_ar": "بر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the aor. is more properly rendered by the present than by the future. ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA rajula qaAy^imN", "text_ar": "لَا رَجُلَ قَايِمٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is not any man standing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mugh:) but when the subst. and epithet are both simple words, and not separated, the latter may be used in three different ways; as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA rajula Zariyfa", "text_ar": "لَا رَجُلَ ظَرِيفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZariyfFA", "text_ar": "ظَرِيفًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZariyfN", "text_ar": "ظَرِيفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; otherwise it must be marfooa or mansoob, but not mebnee: this relates to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA", "text_ar": "لا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "used"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "linafoYi Aljinosi", "text_ar": "لِنَفْىِ الجِنْسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Ibn-'Akeel, p."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "165"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA", "text_ar": "لا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Lest."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakabahu", "text_ar": "رَكَبَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b4-  ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA lahu walaA Ealayohi", "text_ar": "لَا لَهُ وَلَا عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is nothing due to him, nor anything to be demanded of him."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Thus I have rendered this phrase, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "malasaY", "text_ar": "مَلَسَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in three places.) For] when"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA", "text_ar": "لا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a general negative, the context renders it allowable to suppress its subject, as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA Ealayoka", "text_ar": "لَا عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA baA^osa Ealayoka", "text_ar": "لَا بَاْسَ عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and sometimes the predicate, when known, is suppressed, as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA baA^osa", "text_ar": "لَا بَاْسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA$a", "text_ar": "لَاشَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA $aYo'a", "text_ar": "لَا شَىْءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lw$", "text_ar": "لوش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalaA walaA", "text_ar": "كَلَا وَلَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As the time occupied in saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA walaA", "text_ar": "لَا وَلَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. See an ex. in the TA, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lwo*aAn", "text_ar": "لوْذَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA 